cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the information transmission process on communication networks, which is a topic related to network science and information theory. The use of fixed and mobile nodes in the network suggests a focus on network infrastructure and design, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The study of traffic load and network capacity also suggests a focus on optimization and performance analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the consideration of load balancing and rewiring of fixed nodes suggests a focus on system control and management, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
